rs of its acceleration in the late twentieth and early twenty-first centuries: postmodern cultural criticism—including the new historicism, the new cultural history, cultural anthropology, the new pragmatism, and postmodern and postindustrial theory—and digital information technology. What is the relation between the new historicist anecdote and the database field, Liu asks, and can either have a critical function in the age of postmodern historicism? Local Transcendence includes two previously unpublished essays and a synthetic introduction in which Liu traverses from his earlier work on the theory of historicism to his recent studies of information culture to propose a theory of contingent method incorporating a special inflection of history: media history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCriticismxHistoryx20th century. 0aCriticismxHistoryx21st century. 0aCriticismxHistoryy20th century. 0aCriticismxHistoryy21st century. 0aHistoricism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  apostmodern, modernity, future, innovation, formalism, new historicism, subversion, wordsworth, detail, romanticism, transcendence, mourning, memory, commemoration, memorial, spruce goose, remembrance, literature, interdisciplinary, technology, sidney, aesthetics, discourse, history, past, nonfiction, media, art, popular culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226486970423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226486970/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles